
            Video
            Iran's health insurers to pay for sex change operations
            The founder of the Islamic Republic of Iran, Ayatollah Khomeini, passed a fatwa in the 1980s allowing sex-change operations in the country.Up until now, Iran's welfare system paid a small amount toward these operations but they are very costly.Now health insurance companies are obliged to cover all costs.Karen Zarindast reports.Video produced by BBC Persian's Saeedeh Hashemi
                
                        29 May 2012
                    
                
        
